### Full refresh — clears DailyCustomerRevenue, re-aggregates all completed orders.
POST http://localhost:4103/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"DailyCustomerRevenue","trigger":"manual"}

### Inspect the snapshot — one row per customer with completed orders.
GET http://localhost:4103/odata/v4/reporting/DailyCustomerRevenue?$orderby=totalAmount desc

### Partial refresh — first run has no watermark, aggregates all completed orders.
POST http://localhost:4103/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"RecentCustomerRevenue","trigger":"manual"}

### Inspect — mirrors DailyCustomerRevenue on the first run.
GET http://localhost:4103/odata/v4/reporting/RecentCustomerRevenue?$orderby=totalAmount desc

### Insert a new completed order → only the affected customer's aggregate
### row will be rebuilt by the next partial refresh.
POST http://localhost:4103/odata/v4/sales/Orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ID": "O-2001",
    "customerId": "ALFKI",
    "status": "completed",
    "amount": 999.99,
    "placedAt": "2025-02-20",
    "modifiedAt": "2025-02-20T12:00:00Z"
}

### Partial refresh — only re-aggregates customers whose orders moved since
### the tracker's lastSync. Watch `statistics.deleted` == `statistics.created`
### for the single touched customer, while the others stay untouched.
POST http://localhost:4103/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"RecentCustomerRevenue","trigger":"manual"}

GET http://localhost:4103/odata/v4/reporting/RecentCustomerRevenue?$orderby=totalAmount desc

### For comparison — same event forces a full rebuild on the full-refresh pipeline.
POST http://localhost:4103/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"DailyCustomerRevenue","trigger":"manual"}
